<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870728-0108 </DOCNO><HL> Canada to Offer BondsTotaling $561.5                                                  </HL><SO>  </SO><IN> CANDABOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> OTTAWA  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Canadian government said it will offer 750 million Canadian dollars ($561.5 million) of bonds in two issues this week.    The sale will consist of 9 1/4% bonds due July 1992 and 9 3/4% bonds due October 1997. Offering terms are to be announced today.    The Bank of Canada has agreed to buy at least 50 million dollars of the bonds. The remainder will be available to investors.    Proceeds will be used for general purposes. </TEXT></DOC>